  "prompt": "What is the origin of Snow White?",
  "response": "The story of Snow White has its origins in a German fairy tale called \"Snow White\" (originally \"Schneewittchen\") collected by the Brothers Grimm and published in their famous anthology, \"Grimm's Fairy Tales,\" in 1812. The tale is believed to have roots in various folklore and oral traditions that predate the Grimms' version.\n\nThe central elements of the story\u2014such as the wicked stepmother, the seven dwarfs, and the poisoned apple\u2014are prevalent in many variations of the tale across different cultures. Some historians suggest that there are similarities to older legends and stories, including those found in Celtic and Norse mythology, which feature themes of jealousy, beauty, and the supernatural.\n\nIn addition to the Brothers Grimm's version, there have been various adaptations and retellings of Snow White in literature, theater, and film. The most famous adaptation is probably Disney's animated film \"Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs,\" released in 1937, which helped popularize the story worldwide and introduced a new, iconic interpretation of the characters and themes.",
